  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development and is described in the technical report narrative, confirming that impeller rotational speed and inlet flow rate are the dominant drivers of predicted hemolysis index. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed. Decision: Accepted.",
